treatments.name: RMT Prenatal Massage 45 min
treatments.description:
As you grow towards your due date, your body has to sustain an incredible amount of change. Sometimes these changes create pain, swelling and diminished mobility. Regular Massage Therapy can help you grow into your new body and reduce and manage uncomfortable symptoms.

Pregnancy massage is a great means of ensuring that your changing body adapts comfortably to your growing bundle of joy.
Massage during pregnancy can help your body adjust to the changes of pregnancy. Helping you sleep better, allowing you to be more mobile and relax you mentally and physically. As you progress through pregnancy there is an increase in blood flow, increase in function of all your organs (heart, lung, liver) and of course the obvious tired, achy muscles. Massage therapy can help optimize your health and wellbeing during the entirety of your pregnancy.

A typical massage session takes at least 60 minutes and you will be comfortably positioned on your side.

treatments.name: Osteopathy
treatments.description:
Osteopathic medicine is helpful to treat the following conditions: 
Back pain.
Back of Head, neck and shoulder pain,  joints and limbs. 
Neuralgia and sinus pain.
Arthritis and rheumatism. 
Nerve irritation
Spondylosis & tension pain. 
Stress related conditions. 
Digestive and breathing problems.
Headaches and Migraine. 
Sports injuries. 
Repetitive strain injuries.
Whiplash injuries.
Pregnancy and associated symptoms e.g. nausea, heartburn, backache, etc.
Colic and sleep problems in babies.
Restriction of motion within the body is often due to traumatic or postural stress causing muscle tension and pull on fascias in the area; this affects the tissue around it. The continual movement of bodily fluids is also essential for maintaining well being. When this is not working, a state of congestion of circulation develops. This impairs the delivery of oxygen and nutrients and removal of waste products from the tissues which creates discomfort and pain. This often may be felt in an area not that closely associated to the original problem.
Osteopathic practitioners use specialized skills to identify restrictions and tensions of the tissues in your body. Their specific techniques ease those restrictions, which allows for normal physiology to continue.

What Does the Lymphatic System Do?

The lymphatic system is composed of lymph nodes, fluid (known as lymph), vessels that transport the lymph and organs that consist of lymph tissue such as the spleen, small intestine, and throat. Similar to how veins and capillaries work to move blood through the circulatory system, the lymphatic system is a network of vessels that moves lymph from tissues to the bloodstream. Lymph is made of white blood cells that attack bacteria within the blood and it’s made of intestinal fluid that holds protein and fat. Your lymph nodes are formed in clusters throughout the body in areas like the centre of the chest, groin, the armpit and your neck. This system is a key player in the body’s immune system because it helps to move waste and toxins out of your tissues so that they’re flushed out. If the lymphatic system isn’t functioning properly, you’ll experience a variety of health issues.

There are two main methods to a TMJ massage, the first being extra-orally, or outside of the mouth. When working outside, your therapist will focus on your chewing muscles around the face. 

The second method is intra-orally, or in the mouth. Prior to beginning intra-oral massage, your practitioner will put on a pair of gloves.

Deanna shared that she breaks the intra-oral massage down into sections to allow for breaks for clients to swallow. The sensation can be quite intense because we use these muscles regularly but do not often receive or self-administer massage there. 

When in the mouth, she begins in between the cheek and teeth, with the muscles at the back of the mouth. Then she moves to the outside of the teeth and massages the medial pterygoid, which is the muscle that moves our jaw from side to side when we are chewing

Thermography Pre-Imaging Instructions
Note: Patients who are post operative or have had any form of allopathic cancer treatment must wait until three (3) months has passed, nursing mothers must wait until two (2) months has passed from the date of completion before imaging. Patients who have received IV treatment must wait one day and dye injected imaging must wait one week.
Before you arrive for your thermographic examination, certain protocols must be followed in order to ensure that your images reflect accurate information.
 Covid vaccination must be 4 weeks prior
 Cosmetic treatments (i.e. botox, laser, fillers etc.) or tattoos to body areas being imaged must
wait 3 months post final application.
 No tanning salon or direct sun exposure (especially sunburn) to the body areas being imaged 3
days prior to the exam.
 Minimal use of lotions, creams, perfumes/colognes, powders or deodorant on the areas to be
imaged the day of the exam.
 No shaving or waxing of the areas to be imaged the day of the exam.
 No treatment (chiropractic, acupuncture, TENS, physical therapy, electrical muscle stimulation,
ultrasound, hot or cold pack use) or massage of the areas to be imaged for 24 hours before the
exam.
 No exercise or physical stimulation of the areas to be imaged 4 hours prior to the exam.
 If bathing/showering, it must be no closer than 1 hour before the exam.
 No drinking caffeine or alcohol the day of the exam.
 No eating or drinking hot or cold beverages 2 hours before the exam.
 No smoking for 2 hours before the exam.
 Use your regular medications and supplements as prescribed.
 If you are scheduled for a breast thermogram, the same protocols above applies along with no
physical stimulation of the breasts for 24 hours before the exam. Note: thermography can be performed on nursing mothers if prescribed and post feeding at least 1 hour.
Please note: During the examination you will be disrobed and gowned during part of the examination for both imaging and to allow for the surface temperature of the body to equilibrate with the room. (Clothing will be removed from the waist up for breast exams, and fully for full body scan, except underwear. The buttocks will be exposed so please wear thong or brief type.) No jewelry and hair will be tied back away from the face and neck.

treatments.description:
Dermaplaning and Microneedling are Effective Stand alone treatments. But combined they can produce optimal results. Dermaplaning is a safe and simple skin rejuvenation treatment intended to exfoliate the epidermis and remove facial peach fuzz. It leaves the skin smoother and looking healthier. This exfoliation allows for your skincare products to penetrate more readily into the deeper layers.

Microneedling or collagen induction therapy generate micro-punctures in the skin and stimulates the collagen. It results in a smoother and more youthful appearance. The micropunctures create a controlled injury underneath the surface of the skin, which then sends a wake up call to the collagen to start producing more. The skin plumps and thickens in response to this. Microneedling aims to improve mild to moderate acne scarring, fine lines and wrinkles, rough skin texture, decreases pore size, and tightens lax skin and reduces hyperpigmentation.

treatments.name: RMT Oncology Massage 60 min
treatments.description:
Oncology massage therapy offers a lot of benefits for clients undergoing cancer treatment. 
~Relaxation and stress reduction: Oncology massage can help promote deep relaxation, reduce stress, and provide a sense of comfort and well-being. It can help to calm the nervous system and release tension, allowing patients to experience a greater sense of peace and relaxation.
~Pain and symptom management: Cancer and its treatments can cause various physical symptoms such as pain, fatigue, nausea, and neuropathy. Oncology massage therapy can help alleviate these symptoms by reducing muscle tension, improving circulation, and promoting the release of endorphins, which are natural pain-relieving substances.
~Improved sleep: Many cancer patients experience disruptions in their sleep patterns. Oncology massage can help promote better sleep by inducing relaxation, reducing anxiety, and relieving physical discomfort. Quality sleep is vital for the body's natural healing processes.
~Emotional support: A cancer diagnosis and treatment can often bring about emotional distress, anxiety, and depression. Oncology massage therapy provides a safe space for patients to relax, express their emotions, and receive compassionate touch, which can help reduce feelings of isolation and provide emotional support.
~Improved lymphatic flow: Some massage techniques used in oncology massage are specifically designed to support the lymphatic system, which plays a crucial role in immune function. Promoting healthy lymphatic flow can help reduce swelling (lymphedema) and support the body's natural detoxification process.

treatments.name: RMT Lymphatic Drainage Massage 60 Mins
treatments.description:
What Does the Lymphatic System Do?

The lymphatic system is composed of lymph nodes, fluid (known as lymph), vessels that transport the lymph and organs that consist of lymph tissue such as the spleen, small intestine, and throat. Similar to how veins and capillaries work to move blood through the circulatory system, the lymphatic system is a network of vessels that moves lymph from tissues to the bloodstream. Lymph is made of white blood cells that attack bacteria within the blood and it’s made of intestinal fluid that holds protein and fat. Your lymph nodes are formed in clusters throughout the body in areas like the centre of the chest, groin, the armpit and your neck. This system is a key player in the body’s immune system because it helps to move waste and toxins out of your tissues so that they’re flushed out. If the lymphatic system isn’t functioning properly, you’ll experience a variety of health issues. 

How Do I Know If I Need Lymphatic Drainage Treatment?

If you’re experiencing any of the symptoms below, your body may be encountering toxin overload which means you could benefit from a lymphatic drainage massage.

•Chronic sinus infections
•Swelling in your fingers
•Allergies
•Depression
•Food sensitivities
•Swollen lymph nodes
•Excess weight gain
•Weakened immune system
•Constipation

Dermaplaning and Microneedling are Effective Stand alone treatments. But combined they can produce optimal results. Microneedling or collagen induction therapy generate micro-punctures in the skin and stimulates the collagen. It results in a smoother and more youthful appearance. The micropunctures create a controlled injury underneath the surface of the skin, which then sends a wake up call to the collagen to start producing more. The skin plumps and thickens in response to this. Microneedling aims to improve mild to moderate acne scarring, fine lines and wrinkles, rough skin texture, decreases pore size, and tightens lax skin and reduces hyperpigmentation.

Thermography Pre-Imaging Instructions
Note: Patients who are post operative or have had any form of allopathic cancer treatment must wait until three (3) months has passed, nursing mothers must wait until two (2) months has passed from the date of completion before imaging. Patients who have received IV treatment must wait one day and dye injected imaging must wait one week.
Before you arrive for your thermographic examination, certain protocols must be followed in order to ensure that your images reflect accurate information.
 Covid vaccination must be 4 weeks prior
 Cosmetic treatments (i.e. botox, laser, fillers etc.) or tattoos to body areas being imaged must
wait 3 months post final application.
 No tanning salon or direct sun exposure (especially sunburn) to the body areas being imaged 3
days prior to the exam.
 Minimal use of lotions, creams, perfumes/colognes, powders or deodorant on the areas to be
imaged the day of the exam.
 No shaving or waxing of the areas to be imaged the day of the exam.
 No treatment (chiropractic, acupuncture, TENS, physical therapy, electrical muscle stimulation,
ultrasound, hot or cold pack use) or massage of the areas to be imaged for 24 hours before the
exam.
 No exercise or physical stimulation of the areas to be imaged 4 hours prior to the exam.
 If bathing/showering, it must be no closer than 1 hour before the exam.
 No drinking caffeine or alcohol the day of the exam.
 No eating or drinking hot or cold beverages 2 hours before the exam.
 No smoking for 2 hours before the exam.
 Use your regular medications and supplements as prescribed.
 If you are scheduled for a breast thermogram, the same protocols above applies along with no
physical stimulation of the breasts for 24 hours before the exam. Note: thermography can be performed on nursing mothers if prescribed and post feeding at least 1 hour.
Please note: During the examination you will be disrobed and gowned during part of the examination for both imaging and to allow for the surface temperature of the body to equilibrate with the room. (Clothing will be removed from the waist up for breast exams, and fully for full body scan, except underwear. The buttocks will be exposed so please wear thong or brief type.) Thermography Pre-Imaging Instructions
Note: Patients who are post operative or have had any form of allopathic cancer treatment must wait until three (3) months has passed, nursing mothers must wait until two (2) months has passed from the date of completion before imaging. Patients who have received IV treatment must wait one day and dye injected imaging must wait one week.
Before you arrive for your thermographic examination, certain protocols must be followed in order to ensure that your images reflect accurate information.
 Covid vaccination must be 4 weeks prior
 Cosmetic treatments (i.e. botox, laser, fillers etc.) or tattoos to body areas being imaged must
wait 3 months post final application.
 No tanning salon or direct sun exposure (especially sunburn) to the body areas being imaged 3
days prior to the exam.
 Minimal use of lotions, creams, perfumes/colognes, powders or deodorant on the areas to be
imaged the day of the exam.
 No shaving or waxing of the areas to be imaged the day of the exam.
 No treatment (chiropractic, acupuncture, TENS, physical therapy, electrical muscle stimulation,
ultrasound, hot or cold pack use) or massage of the areas to be imaged for 24 hours before the
exam.
 No exercise or physical stimulation of the areas to be imaged 4 hours prior to the exam.
 If bathing/showering, it must be no closer than 1 hour before the exam.
 No drinking caffeine or alcohol the day of the exam.
 No eating or drinking hot or cold beverages 2 hours before the exam.
 No smoking for 2 hours before the exam.
 Use your regular medications and supplements as prescribed.
 If you are scheduled for a breast thermogram, the same protocols above applies along with no
physical stimulation of the breasts for 24 hours before the exam. Note: thermography can be performed on nursing mothers if prescribed and post feeding at least 1 hour.
Please note: During the examination you will be disrobed and gowned during part of the examination for both imaging and to allow for the surface temperature of the body to equilibrate with the room. (Clothing will be removed from the waist up for breast exams, and fully for full body scan, except underwear. The buttocks will be exposed so please wear thong or brief type.) No jewelry and hair will be tied back away from the face and neck.
If you have any questions, please contact our office by email info@healthscan.ca

treatments.description:
Thai massage

Thai Massage is an ancient and dynamic bodywork therapy in which the practitioner skillfully places the client into a series of yoga-like postures and stretches while applying compression techniques by palm, thumb, elbow or foot pressure linked through slow and mindful movement.

The Thai Massage is performed on comfortable floor mats wearing loose yet comfortable clothing that allows for movement. Thai Massage is a very individual experience in the hands of a skilled practitioner, each session is individually customized and tailored to meet specific client needs, ranging from relaxing, passive, slow palm massage for stress reduction, to an energetic, deep work massage using elbows and knees to apply stronger presses accompanied by stretching, tractions, and twists. Slow and rhythmic, each posture flows easily into the next. Mild, firm or strong touch techniques are applied to create a powerful, singular, healing experience. A relaxing and rejuvenating form of passive yoga, Tai Chi and Eastern massage techniques combined.

Clients are taken through a full range of motion resulting in an increased sense of well-being and stress relief while stimulating the detoxification process by balancing meridians. Sessions complement all body types and are tailored to the individual needs of each client in Toronto.

It is without oil and more pressure point, more deeper and harder withstretching
